76561198041623135,Recommended,432190,20727092,"Posted: 24 January, 2016",all,bohicette,"I really like this game.  I have bought a few of the indie high/low solitaire games off of Steam, but this is by far the best.PROS:A ton of bang for the buck.  I have been playing this for over a week and have only unlocked 23 states or so.  Being that each state has 10 levels, that's a ton of entertainment value for the price.  Can't say how many levels in total because the USA map doesn't include Alaska or Hawaii.  Hopefully they are included after the 48th state as a bonus, but we shall see.Gameplay is simple but strategic.  It is fun trying to use the powerups at the appropriate times to complete a level.Most levels are fairly easy to complete so you advance, but getting three stars on some of them is quite challenging.  I find myself at times, deliberately not getting the final chef's hat card, just to eek out enough money to get the third star.  Another very fun strategic element.Cute ""story line"" running throughout the game.Nice graphics, and decent music.CONS:Once you get all of the powerups, the store becomes pretty much worthless.  I currently have almost $300K and nothing to spend it on.On the complete level screen, it would be great to have a ""Restart"" button even when you advance.  It is a chore to go back through the map screen, when you only get two out of three stars and want to try the same level over again.Overall a solid indie solitaire game that is well worth the price of admission."
