76561197971341065,Recommended,432190,28233834,"Posted: 7 December, 2016",all,sfnhltb,"Overall a well put together casual solitaire based card game with an engaging theme, and plenty of levels to work through (presumably 50 states x 10 levels each).As you work through levels you earn money by stringing together long sequences or matching suits, which allows you to buy extra bonuses such as being able to see some of the face down cards so you can plan ahead, wild cards which you can use to either extend a streak or save to ensure you can get that last card for the perfect clearance, all of which give you more strategic options and reduce the feeling of just relying on luck to win or lose, which can be the downside of solitaire games.There are a couple of mini games that also pop up randomly (making burgers, fixing leaky pipes, match 3 desserts), they don't really add much but I guess they break things up a bit and they don't take long to clear.If compared to Legends of Solitaire (similar game from the same developer) it is probably even more casual (you can't fail a state as a whole, only individual levels if you don't collect certain highlighted cards), and much more polished."
